page.title: 10ECOLOGY 2
page.content: The most common trees (apart from those on forestry land) are alder, elder, rowan (locally-rodden),birch, sycamore,beech,ash, willow and a few white-beam. There are no oak trees in the area. Bog plants proliferate e.g. water speedwell. The germander speedwell is also found in profusion.Until recently there were vast numbers of giant hogweed plants, but now few are left since the eradication programme started a few years ago. A new sewage works ,using the settlement-tank method,was built by the side of the Bogie in 1978/79. The effluent is pumped to an old quarry by the road where twin tanks allow settlement. The clean water is pumped back to the Bogie. Till that date raw sewage flowed untreated into the river.
